5:
The water sure is rough today. 
I hope it calms down soon.
16:
Hehe, hang in there. The waves are
about to die down.
24:
Changes in the wind and cloud
movements. You've always got to
keep an eye on the horizon—
31:
Wait! Change of course, Captain!
Turn hard to port and pursue that
fishing vessel!
33:
Huh? Don't be ridiculous! Going off
course would cost me my job!
35: Not to worry, Captain. You see this?
38:
That's... You're licensed by the
Gaean government?! Wait, I know
that name...
39:
You're Evelyn! That bounty hunter
everyone's talking about!
41:
That's right. The Gaean government
and I will take full responsibility for
this. Plus there might be something
in it for you if you agree.
44:
All right, then! Hold onto your butts,
everyone!
47:
So you're a bounty hunter. Is that
ship your target?
51:
You've got it. It's a poaching vessel
involved in all sorts of nasty
business, so we're talking about a
pretty hefty bounty.
55:
Are we boarding them head-on?
Something tells me they won't come
quietly...
58:
Don't worry, swashbuckling is kind of
my thing. In fact, it's my job.
62:
If they want to try me, they're more
than welcome to.
66:
Just in case, how about some
backup?
71:
We might as well lend a hand,
considering we're all in the same
boat.
75:
Much appreciated! Of course, we'll
split the bounty fair and square—
80: Ngh! Captain, we need to return fire!
84:
You think this is a pirate ship? We
don't have any cannons!
88: Don't worry. Just get us close!
92:
Now, then. It's time we taught our
graceless foes how it's done...
96: This is how you take a shot!
100:
Good afternoon, my little
rapscallions. Come quietly and
nobody gets hurt.
103:
Th-the hell? Who do you think you
are?!
107:
Whoa, hey! Simmer down a little! 
If you don't stop shooting—
113:
SEE? Everyone, abandon ship! It's
gonna blow any minute!
117:
Throw the unconscious ones into the
ocean! They'll have a better chance
surviving the water than an
explosion!
121:
Is that everyone? We need to bail
NOW!
143:
What am I doing laying around?!
The bounty... Did they get away?
147:
No, we tied them up and left them
with the captain. They'll be handed
over to the Gaean authorities at the
next anchorage.
151:
I suppose that means... you all
pulled me out of the water too.
154:
I guess I was just dreaming when I
saw that mermaid...
161:
Merfolk actually exist? Then that
means, when I was little...
164:
...Wait, no. A merMAID saved me
back then, so it couldn't be this
person...
167:
...Never mind. Thank you for saving
me.
170:
I want to thank you all properly
somehow... But could I ask you one
thing first?
173:
Where am I? And... Who are you
people?
177:
In other words, you have a way of
visiting other worlds?! That's
incredible!
179:
In all my years, this is the first time
I've met anyone with such freedom!
182:
We can go back to my world
anytime, right?
184:
In that case, could you show me
around while we're here?
188:
Of course. Welcome to Starview
Village, Evelyn. We're happy to have
you with us.
192: And I'm happy to be here!
